Package: bacontrees
Title: Bayesian Context Trees for Discrete Sequence Data
Version: 0.0.3.999
Authors@R: 
    person("Victor", "Freguglia", email = "victorfreguglia@gmail.com",
             role = c("aut", "cre"),
             comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6189-4453"))
Description: Models discrete sequential data using Bayesian Context Trees
    (BaConTrees). Context trees, also known as Variable Length Markov
    Chains (VLMCs), are parsimonious Markov models where the order of
    dependence can vary with the observed past. Provides a frequentist
    estimator via the context algorithm with likelihood-ratio pruning
    (fit_vlmc()), a Bayesian Metropolis-Hastings sampler for the posterior
    distribution over context trees (metropolis_vlmc()), simulation
    utilities, and R6 classes exposing the full tree structure for
    building custom algorithms.
